1
00:00:11,359 --> 00:00:12,519
Over ten years ago,

2
00:00:12,800 --> 00:00:14,119
you left without a word,

3
00:00:14,480 --> 00:00:16,160
leaving me to raise the child alone.

4
00:00:17,320 --> 00:00:18,000
And now,

5
00:00:18,879 --> 00:00:20,359
you suddenly show up again.

6
00:00:20,920 --> 00:00:21,879
What the hell do you want?

7
00:00:22,600 --> 00:00:23,280
I'm getting old.

8
00:00:23,760 --> 00:00:25,600
I just want to see my only daughter.

9
00:00:25,600 --> 00:00:26,640
Is that too much to ask?

10
00:00:27,399 --> 00:00:27,920
Ruifen,

11
00:00:28,559 --> 00:00:29,719
I'm begging you, okay?

12
00:00:30,359 --> 00:00:31,679
Don't make me wait until I die

13
00:00:31,679 --> 00:00:34,000
without ever hearing the child call me Dad.

14
00:00:43,439 --> 00:00:44,439
A man is escorting me?

15
00:00:45,119 --> 00:00:47,039
Swap him out for a female officer.

16
00:01:01,719 --> 00:01:02,880
Cyanosis on the lip mucosa,

17
00:01:05,120 --> 00:01:06,439
clear cyanosis at the fingertips.

18
00:01:07,319 --> 00:01:09,280
Classic signs of acute circulatory arrest.

19
00:01:10,920 --> 00:01:12,599
No defensive wounds on the body.

20
00:01:14,120 --> 00:01:17,120
Likely sudden death from cardiac arrest.

21
00:01:17,359 --> 00:01:19,239
We'll need the autopsy for the exact cause.

22
00:01:22,200 --> 00:01:22,719
Forceps.

23
00:01:36,840 --> 00:01:39,000
It was like she was playing the role

24
00:01:39,000 --> 00:01:40,200
of a grieving widow.

25
00:01:40,640 --> 00:01:42,239
If I hadn't been with her the whole time,

26
00:01:42,239 --> 00:01:43,599
I'd actually believe

27
00:01:43,599 --> 00:01:44,920
she was the one who killed her husband.

28
00:01:45,120 --> 00:01:46,159
Just like that...

29
00:01:46,719 --> 00:01:47,200
Just like...

30
00:01:47,599 --> 00:01:48,760
Just like that Pan Jinlian.

31
00:01:49,040 --> 00:01:50,680
The autopsy confirmed

32
00:01:50,959 --> 00:01:53,239
Wang Kechen died of a heart attack.

33
00:01:53,239 --> 00:01:55,040
And at that time, you happened to be with her.

34
00:01:55,560 --> 00:01:57,560
You're her perfect alibi.

35
00:01:58,560 --> 00:01:59,959
Doesn't that make it even more suspicious?

36
00:02:00,239 --> 00:02:01,719
Sure, I admit

37
00:02:02,159 --> 00:02:03,200
I'm a good-looking guy.

38
00:02:03,359 --> 00:02:04,959
Other women fall for me easily.

39
00:02:04,959 --> 00:02:06,319
But I could feel it.

40
00:02:07,120 --> 00:02:08,800
When she was clinging to me that night,

41
00:02:09,560 --> 00:02:11,319
she definitely wasn't into me for real.

42
00:02:11,680 --> 00:02:13,879
She just wanted to keep me as a witness.

43
00:02:13,879 --> 00:02:14,479
Yu Tianfang,

44
00:02:14,879 --> 00:02:16,000
I need to correct you here.

45
00:02:16,719 --> 00:02:19,000
This is a routine police inquiry.

46
00:02:19,360 --> 00:02:21,199
You can't just state your own delusions.

47
00:02:21,199 --> 00:02:22,639
Do you have any actual evidence?

48
00:02:23,080 --> 00:02:25,840
They say women have a sharp sixth sense.

49
00:02:26,199 --> 00:02:27,479
Well, us men aren't bad either.

50
00:02:27,800 --> 00:02:29,520
I'm telling you, she was setting me up.

51
00:02:30,919 --> 00:02:31,479
Captain Chu,

52
00:02:31,639 --> 00:02:32,560
about Xu Lingling,

53
00:02:32,560 --> 00:02:33,919
we've already issued a request for assistance.

54
00:02:33,919 --> 00:02:35,280
We're also looking into her household registration

55
00:02:35,479 --> 00:02:36,520
and her social connections.

56
00:02:36,680 --> 00:02:37,599
Barring any surprises,

57
00:02:37,599 --> 00:02:38,560
we'll have results soon.

58
00:02:38,759 --> 00:02:39,919
We came prepared.

59
00:02:40,360 --> 00:02:41,680
Body disposal notice,

60
00:02:42,360 --> 00:02:44,039
medical certificate of death.

61
00:02:44,919 --> 00:02:46,599
We'll take these to Xu Lingling

62
00:02:46,599 --> 00:02:47,439
and see how she reacts.

63
00:02:48,240 --> 00:02:49,639
Then we'll get reacquainted

64
00:02:49,639 --> 00:02:50,479
with this Xu Lingling.

65
00:02:52,479 --> 00:02:53,360
Ms. Xu,

66
00:02:53,360 --> 00:02:54,479
we're very sorry

67
00:02:54,680 --> 00:02:55,680
about your husband's passing.

68
00:02:55,680 --> 00:02:57,479
You all did everything you could to save him.

69
00:02:57,960 --> 00:02:58,879
I'm very grateful.

70
00:03:00,439 --> 00:03:01,240
Unfortunately,

71
00:03:01,479 --> 00:03:02,759
luck just wasn't on his side.

72
00:03:03,159 --> 00:03:04,599
Did he have a history of heart disease?

73
00:03:04,719 --> 00:03:05,319
Yes.

74
00:03:05,919 --> 00:03:07,120
The doctor prescribed him medication,

75
00:03:07,120 --> 00:03:08,599
but he found it to be a hassle.

76
00:03:09,280 --> 00:03:11,120
Sometimes he took it, sometimes he didn't.

77
00:03:11,599 --> 00:03:12,560
There was nothing I could do.

78
00:03:13,080 --> 00:03:15,120
That night was your wedding anniversary,

79
00:03:15,560 --> 00:03:17,120
yet he was with another woman.

80
00:03:17,719 --> 00:03:19,919
And you were with the resort manager, Yu Tianfang.

81
00:03:20,520 --> 00:03:21,599
Could you explain

82
00:03:21,599 --> 00:03:22,879
what exactly was going on?

83
00:03:23,479 --> 00:03:25,479
If I said we loved each other deeply,

84
00:03:25,800 --> 00:03:26,840
you probably wouldn't believe me.

85
00:03:27,800 --> 00:03:29,439
But my husband was always a womanizer.

86
00:03:29,960 --> 00:03:31,199
I'd already gotten used to it.

87
00:03:31,960 --> 00:03:33,479
As long as we were each happy,

88
00:03:34,120 --> 00:03:35,280
we didn't interfere with each other.

89
00:03:35,680 --> 00:03:36,520
Ms. Xu,

90
00:03:37,120 --> 00:03:38,360
the night your husband died,

91
00:03:38,360 --> 00:03:40,560
he was targeted by a pair of honey trap regulars.

92
00:03:40,960 --> 00:03:42,199
To get to the bottom of this,

93
00:03:42,639 --> 00:03:43,919
we'll need to learn more

94
00:03:43,919 --> 00:03:45,240
about your husband.

95
00:03:45,240 --> 00:03:46,120
We hope you'll cooperate.

96
00:03:48,400 --> 00:03:49,280
He was simply

97
00:03:49,280 --> 00:03:51,280
the kind of man women fell for easily.

98
00:03:52,120 --> 00:03:52,919
Honestly,

99
00:03:53,280 --> 00:03:54,360
if nothing had gone wrong,

100
00:03:55,000 --> 00:03:56,120
the honey trap girl

101
00:03:56,120 --> 00:03:57,400
might not have been able to swindle his money.

102
00:03:58,039 --> 00:03:59,000
But he very likely

103
00:03:59,319 --> 00:04:00,240
would have stolen the girl's heart.

104
00:04:03,719 --> 00:04:05,000
So as his wife,

105
00:04:05,479 --> 00:04:06,439
wouldn't you be jealous?

106
00:04:09,840 --> 00:04:11,439
Since I chose to marry him,

107
00:04:11,840 --> 00:04:13,199
I accept everything about him.

108
00:04:16,680 --> 00:04:17,399
Ms. Xu,

109
00:04:18,439 --> 00:04:19,800
Can we talk about your marriage history?

110
00:04:20,399 --> 00:04:21,240
As far as we know,

111
00:04:21,800 --> 00:04:22,439
Wang Kechen

112
00:04:22,439 --> 00:04:23,800
wasn't your first husband.

113
00:04:24,680 --> 00:04:26,519
Looks like you've dug it all up.

114
00:04:27,120 --> 00:04:28,319
Your first husband

115
00:04:28,480 --> 00:04:29,399
was electrocuted in the rain

116
00:04:29,399 --> 00:04:30,720
while wading through water.

117
00:04:31,360 --> 00:04:32,360
Your second husband

118
00:04:32,560 --> 00:04:34,360
died accidentally from gas poisoning.

119
00:04:34,600 --> 00:04:35,959
And now, your third husband

120
00:04:36,240 --> 00:04:37,600
suddenly died of a heart attack.

121
00:04:38,120 --> 00:04:39,680
Isn't that a bit too coincidental?

122
00:04:40,839 --> 00:04:42,600
Memories are always painful.

123
00:04:43,000 --> 00:04:44,879
I don't want to talk about the past.

124
00:04:45,079 --> 00:04:46,720
I wasn't there when any of them died.

125
00:04:47,040 --> 00:04:47,800
Besides,

126
00:04:48,160 --> 00:04:50,560
the police issued their death certificates.

127
00:04:51,360 --> 00:04:53,519
Though many say I have the Husband-killer curse,

128
00:04:54,199 --> 00:04:55,240
but surely you, the police,

129
00:04:55,560 --> 00:04:57,560
wouldn't use that as evidence, right?

130
00:04:57,959 --> 00:04:59,439
Have you never once suspected

131
00:05:00,040 --> 00:05:01,000
that your husband's death

132
00:05:01,000 --> 00:05:01,800
wasn't an accident?

133
00:05:05,079 --> 00:05:06,399
If you think

134
00:05:06,399 --> 00:05:08,319
Wang Kechen was murdered,

135
00:05:08,319 --> 00:05:09,560
then the one you should investigate

136
00:05:09,560 --> 00:05:10,800
is Bai Ruifen,

137
00:05:11,000 --> 00:05:11,959
not me.

138
00:05:12,519 --> 00:05:14,480
You mean Bai Ruifen, the resort's owner?

139
00:05:17,160 --> 00:05:19,240
Wang Kechen and Bai Ruifen have known each other

140
00:05:19,560 --> 00:05:20,759
far longer than I have known him.

141
00:05:20,959 --> 00:05:22,000
As far as I know,

142
00:05:22,319 --> 00:05:24,720
Wang Kechen didn't just abandon Bai Ruifen,

143
00:05:24,720 --> 00:05:26,360
he also abandoned their daughter.

144
00:05:27,399 --> 00:05:28,240
That

145
00:05:28,600 --> 00:05:30,800
should count as a motive for murder, right?

146
00:05:31,480 --> 00:05:32,240
A daughter?

147
00:05:33,879 --> 00:05:35,000
Don't forget,

148
00:05:35,160 --> 00:05:37,160
this is Bai Ruifen's turf.

149
00:06:00,480 --> 00:06:01,160
Boss Bai.

150
00:06:05,439 --> 00:06:06,360
Qiqi.

151
00:06:06,439 --> 00:06:07,399
What are you doing here?

152
00:06:07,879 --> 00:06:08,519
Wait—

153
00:06:09,199 --> 00:06:10,000
What are you doing?

154
00:06:10,680 --> 00:06:12,000
None of your business.

155
00:06:18,040 --> 00:06:19,079
What did you take?

156
00:06:19,240 --> 00:06:19,560
Wait—

157
00:06:45,079 --> 00:06:46,120
Wang Kechen.

158
00:06:47,399 --> 00:06:49,040
You've really put me through hell.

159
00:06:53,360 --> 00:06:54,000
Come in.

160
00:07:01,199 --> 00:07:02,800
Things finally quieted down.

161
00:07:03,120 --> 00:07:04,480
Why are you back again?

162
00:07:04,639 --> 00:07:05,240
Bai Ruifen.

163
00:07:05,399 --> 00:07:07,600
Xu Lingling extorted 5 million from you.

164
00:07:07,600 --> 00:07:08,480
Why didn't you report it?

165
00:07:09,920 --> 00:07:10,720
You don't actually suspect

166
00:07:10,720 --> 00:07:12,240
that I killed Wang Kechen, do you?

167
00:07:12,560 --> 00:07:14,160
I just wanted to keep things quiet.

168
00:07:14,399 --> 00:07:16,040
How did I end up a suspect instead?

169
00:07:16,879 --> 00:07:17,680
Someone said

170
00:07:18,240 --> 00:07:20,240
Wang Kechen abandoned you and your daughter.

171
00:07:20,720 --> 00:07:22,399
What's your real relationship with him?

172
00:07:26,079 --> 00:07:27,040
At this point,

173
00:07:27,600 --> 00:07:28,920
there's nothing left to hide.

174
00:07:30,720 --> 00:07:32,079
If he hadn't come to the resort,

175
00:07:32,600 --> 00:07:33,240
maybe

176
00:07:33,240 --> 00:07:34,600
none of this would have happened.

177
00:07:37,040 --> 00:07:38,160
Over twenty years ago,

178
00:07:38,519 --> 00:07:39,560
not long after I got married,

179
00:07:39,959 --> 00:07:41,439
my husband died in an accident.

180
00:07:41,879 --> 00:07:42,920
Then I lost my job.

181
00:07:43,639 --> 00:07:45,040
I was too poor to even eat.

182
00:07:45,639 --> 00:07:46,800
So I had to work as a dancer.

183
00:07:47,240 --> 00:07:48,399
And at the Dance hall,

184
00:07:48,759 --> 00:07:50,000
I met Wang Kechen.

185
00:07:50,199 --> 00:07:51,160
Back then,

186
00:07:51,480 --> 00:07:52,439
being with him

187
00:07:52,439 --> 00:07:53,639
made me genuinely happy.

188
00:07:54,000 --> 00:07:55,560
I even had a daughter with him.

189
00:07:56,360 --> 00:07:57,480
But he got busier and busier.

190
00:07:58,079 --> 00:07:59,759
Barely saw him a few times a month.

191
00:08:01,600 --> 00:08:02,839
Only later did I find out

192
00:08:03,160 --> 00:08:05,120
that Wang Kechen not only had a wife,

193
00:08:05,240 --> 00:08:06,959
but a bunch of mistresses too.

194
00:08:08,240 --> 00:08:09,800
I wanted a proper status for my daughter.

195
00:08:10,040 --> 00:08:11,040
So I fought with him about it.

196
00:08:11,519 --> 00:08:12,480
He sweet-talked me, promising

197
00:08:13,079 --> 00:08:14,319
he'd definitely marry me.

198
00:08:15,160 --> 00:08:16,360
But as time went on,

199
00:08:17,639 --> 00:08:19,120
I eventually gave up hope.

200
00:08:19,920 --> 00:08:21,720
I demanded a huge settlement from him.

201
00:08:22,480 --> 00:08:24,759
Tore down the Old Bai Residence and rebuilt it.

202
00:08:26,759 --> 00:08:27,480
Step by step,

203
00:08:28,560 --> 00:08:29,480
that's how I got to where I am today.

204
00:08:30,560 --> 00:08:31,360
Do you hate him?

205
00:08:31,959 --> 00:08:33,320
It'd be a lie to say I don't.

206
00:08:33,519 --> 00:08:35,080
After all, I truly loved him.

207
00:08:35,320 --> 00:08:36,679
But he made up for it with money.

208
00:08:36,960 --> 00:08:38,159
And because he was generous enough,

209
00:08:38,840 --> 00:08:40,559
with all those mistresses coming and going,

210
00:08:41,080 --> 00:08:42,080
we all ended things on decent terms.

211
00:08:42,759 --> 00:08:43,679
Who is your daughter?

212
00:08:44,000 --> 00:08:44,919
What's her name?

213
00:08:45,559 --> 00:08:47,000
My daughter has nothing to do with this case.

214
00:08:47,279 --> 00:08:48,559
I don't want to drag her into it.

215
00:08:52,159 --> 00:08:52,879
Bai Ruifen.

216
00:08:53,240 --> 00:08:54,240
Why did you keep this from me?

217
00:08:55,080 --> 00:08:56,559
You never told me who my real father was.

218
00:08:57,759 --> 00:08:58,799
Now he's dead.

219
00:08:59,639 --> 00:09:01,399
I never even got the chance to meet him.

220
00:09:01,960 --> 00:09:02,559
He Siqi.

221
00:09:03,279 --> 00:09:04,559
So you're Bai Ruifen's daughter.

222
00:09:05,799 --> 00:09:07,519
She doesn't deserve to be called a mother.

223
00:09:07,919 --> 00:09:09,440
Qiqi, don't talk like that.

224
00:09:09,840 --> 00:09:10,679
What if

225
00:09:10,879 --> 00:09:12,360
Boss Bai has her own reasons?

226
00:09:12,879 --> 00:09:14,080
She said it was for my own good.

227
00:09:15,000 --> 00:09:16,240
To find me a good Dad.

228
00:09:16,720 --> 00:09:17,759
She remarried three times.

229
00:09:18,320 --> 00:09:19,679
I moved from home to home,

230
00:09:20,039 --> 00:09:21,279
changed surname after surname.

231
00:09:21,879 --> 00:09:23,320
None of those men ever satisfied her.

232
00:09:23,639 --> 00:09:25,639
She wouldn't even let me know my real father.

233
00:09:25,639 --> 00:09:26,600
Tell me!

234
00:09:27,480 --> 00:09:29,360
Shouldn't my name be Wang Siqi?

235
00:09:31,039 --> 00:09:31,919
I'm sorry.

236
00:09:33,559 --> 00:09:34,960
I didn't mean to.

237
00:09:37,600 --> 00:09:38,360
Tell me.

238
00:09:39,600 --> 00:09:40,399
That day,

239
00:09:40,960 --> 00:09:42,360
when you met Wang Kechen,

240
00:09:42,879 --> 00:09:43,799
did he know

241
00:09:44,399 --> 00:09:45,519
that I'm his biological daughter?

242
00:10:13,879 --> 00:10:14,360
Young lady.

243
00:10:14,759 --> 00:10:16,039
So you're a musician.

244
00:10:18,759 --> 00:10:19,440
You...

245
00:10:20,000 --> 00:10:21,039
are Boss Bai's friend.

246
00:10:21,360 --> 00:10:22,080
Do you still remember?

247
00:10:22,080 --> 00:10:23,480
I held you when you were little.

248
00:10:24,200 --> 00:10:26,200
When I was little, my mom was busy with work,

249
00:10:26,519 --> 00:10:28,480
so she often left me with the neighbors.

250
00:10:28,960 --> 00:10:30,279
You've suffered, my child.

251
00:10:30,600 --> 00:10:32,039
If only I'd been there.

252
00:10:33,159 --> 00:10:33,919
Wang Kechen!

253
00:10:35,480 --> 00:10:37,120
Aren't we celebrating our anniversary?

254
00:10:37,279 --> 00:10:38,559
Come on, let's talk.

255
00:10:39,200 --> 00:10:40,360
I... I'm with the child...

256
00:10:40,840 --> 00:10:42,120
Don't bother the young people.

257
00:10:42,279 --> 00:10:43,120
Don't bother the kid.

258
00:10:43,120 --> 00:10:43,799
Stop pulling me!

259
00:10:43,799 --> 00:10:44,320
Come on!

260
00:10:48,679 --> 00:10:49,679
All my life,

261
00:10:50,440 --> 00:10:52,080
I just wanted to know who my real father was.

262
00:10:53,440 --> 00:10:55,559
But I never even got to talk to him properly.

263
00:10:56,480 --> 00:10:57,080
Why?

264
00:10:57,960 --> 00:10:58,759
Between the two of you,

265
00:10:59,919 --> 00:11:01,240
what kind of grudge could there be?

266
00:11:03,080 --> 00:11:04,840
He was an irresponsible playboy.

267
00:11:05,240 --> 00:11:06,639
I thought it'd be better for you

268
00:11:06,639 --> 00:11:07,840
not knowing he existed.

269
00:11:17,320 --> 00:11:17,919
Boss Bai.

270
00:11:18,559 --> 00:11:19,840
Calm yourself down first.

271
00:11:22,759 --> 00:11:23,759
Then go on.

272
00:11:23,759 --> 00:11:25,080
What happened between you two?

273
00:11:29,000 --> 00:11:29,600
Ruifen.

274
00:11:30,240 --> 00:11:31,399
I'm begging you, alright?

275
00:11:32,000 --> 00:11:33,360
Don't make me wait until I die

276
00:11:33,360 --> 00:11:34,320
without ever hearing the child

277
00:11:34,320 --> 00:11:35,600
call me Dad.

278
00:11:37,120 --> 00:11:37,799
Stay here for now.

279
00:11:38,320 --> 00:11:39,200
Let me think it over.

280
00:11:39,759 --> 00:11:41,360
I'll figure out how to arrange a meeting.

281
00:11:42,559 --> 00:11:43,200
Ruifen.

282
00:11:43,759 --> 00:11:45,000
You're still the best to me.

283
00:11:45,399 --> 00:11:46,039
Give me a hug.

284
00:11:48,600 --> 00:11:50,120
What's all this hugging about?

285
00:11:50,720 --> 00:11:51,840
What are you doing?

286
00:11:52,399 --> 00:11:53,480
What child?

287
00:11:54,279 --> 00:11:55,679
You two have a child together?

288
00:11:55,919 --> 00:11:56,960
She's my child.

289
00:11:57,679 --> 00:11:58,960
Nothing to do with him.

290
00:12:01,759 --> 00:12:02,360
Hey.

291
00:12:02,559 --> 00:12:03,159
Hey.

292
00:12:08,240 --> 00:12:08,799
Ruifen.

293
00:12:09,919 --> 00:12:12,240
She really looks like you when you were young.

294
00:12:13,080 --> 00:12:14,919
Remember when we were at the big Dance hall?

295
00:12:15,519 --> 00:12:16,360
Back then,

296
00:12:18,799 --> 00:12:19,960
that was really something.

297
00:12:20,919 --> 00:12:22,200
Looks like what you care about

298
00:12:22,360 --> 00:12:23,720
is those younger years,

299
00:12:24,120 --> 00:12:25,080
not me.

300
00:12:25,840 --> 00:12:26,840
Who doesn't love being young?

301
00:12:26,840 --> 00:12:27,399
Honey.

302
00:12:27,960 --> 00:12:28,639
I'm thirsty.

303
00:12:29,200 --> 00:12:30,200
I want some juice.

304
00:12:31,000 --> 00:12:31,519
I'll go get it for you.

305
00:12:32,000 --> 00:12:32,639
This way.

306
00:12:32,879 --> 00:12:33,320
This way.

307
00:12:33,320 --> 00:12:33,919
This way, this way.

308
00:12:33,919 --> 00:12:34,960
This way.

309
00:12:35,399 --> 00:12:35,759
Over here.

310
00:12:35,759 --> 00:12:36,159
Go on, go on.

311
00:12:36,159 --> 00:12:37,080
Okay, okay, okay.

312
00:12:37,080 --> 00:12:37,720
Okay, okay.

313
00:12:38,360 --> 00:12:39,080
Room temperature, okay?

314
00:12:39,279 --> 00:12:39,799
Got it.

315
00:12:40,399 --> 00:12:41,200
Orange juice.

316
00:12:41,519 --> 00:12:42,679
Got... got it.

317
00:12:45,080 --> 00:12:47,480
Don't think just because you had a daughter with him,

318
00:12:47,480 --> 00:12:48,879
that makes you so special.

319
00:12:49,919 --> 00:12:52,799
The one he loves most now is me.

320
00:12:53,360 --> 00:12:54,759
I'm his wife.

321
00:12:58,240 --> 00:12:58,919
Don't worry.

322
00:12:59,679 --> 00:13:01,360
I lost interest in him long ago.

323
00:13:01,960 --> 00:13:03,080
If you have the time,

324
00:13:03,559 --> 00:13:04,399
you'd better keep an eye on

325
00:13:04,399 --> 00:13:06,080
that womanizing husband of yours.

326
00:13:07,000 --> 00:13:08,240
My feelings for Wang Kechen?

327
00:13:08,600 --> 00:13:09,720
I let them go a long time ago.

328
00:13:10,000 --> 00:13:11,399
It's Xu Lingling who

329
00:13:11,600 --> 00:13:13,279
can't seem to let go.

330
00:13:20,159 --> 00:13:20,679
Chu Feng!

331
00:13:21,039 --> 00:13:22,240
Xu Lingling has left the resort.

332
00:13:22,559 --> 00:13:23,480
She must be trying to run.

333
00:13:23,480 --> 00:13:24,399
Hurry, go catch her!
